The article consists of a collection of statements from various politicians and officials expressing their support for President Trump's decision to reduce the size of two national monuments in Utah. They believe that this decision restores balance and allows for more local input in determining the appropriate use of public lands. They also argue that it aligns with the intent of the Antiquities Act and protects the economy and livelihoods of the local communities. The officials express their gratitude to President Trump for listening to their concerns and taking action.